Interface CellReader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JDBCCellReader

    public interface CellReader
    Abstract source of tabulated cell data.
    Since:
    1.2

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void close()
      Complete the transfer.
      String[] getHeaderRow()
      Return the header row.
      String[] readDataRow()

    • Method Detail

      • getHeaderRow

        String[] getHeaderRow()
                      throws AnaplanAPIException,
                             IOException
        Return the header row. This may be called multiple times, but will return the same value.
        Returns:
        If there is no header information available, then null; otherwise, an array of string header values, one per column.
        Throws:
        AnaplanAPIException
        IOException

      • readDataRow

        String[] readDataRow()
                     throws AnaplanAPIException,
                            IOException
        Read and return the next row of data.
        Returns:
        If there is no more data to be read, then null; otherwise, an array of string cell values, one per column.
        Throws:
        AnaplanAPIException
        IOException

      • close

        void close()
           throws AnaplanAPIException,
                  IOException
        Complete the transfer. Any resources associated with the reader instance are released.
        Throws:
        AnaplanAPIException
        IOException
